## Slash commands

This project does not maintain a separate `.claude/commands/` directory. Use the plugin's commands directly, or read the project prompts at `.github/prompts/*.prompt.md` and execute them as instructions to Claude.

## Non-negotiables

See `CONTRIBUTING.md` and `.github/instructions/README.md`. The most important rules:

- Single source of truth — improve existing files, never duplicate
- Code contribution intake before implementation
- TDD red-green-refactor for any non-trivial change
- Quality gates above must pass before any work is "done"
- Capability-driven layout — never dump into `core/`, `utils/`, `helpers/`, `lib/`
- ADR for any decision a new contributor would otherwise have to reverse-engineer
